# harness/intake-profiles.config — intake profile presets (P6b).
#
# Deployed enforcement-protected file: agent edits are floor-denied; changes are authored as sandbox/
# candidates and human-spliced under FORGE_ALLOW_HOOK_EDIT=1 (audit-logged).
#
# `intake.sh start --profile <name>` selects a preset that shapes intake ERGONOMICS only. A profile is
# ADVISORY: it is recorded in the spec Header and the intake sentinel, and surfaced as a hint at scaffold
# time — nothing mechanical keys on it. The acceptance gate is PROFILE-BLIND (it never reads this file),
# and the catastrophic-category floor (cmd_ratify G3) is INDEPENDENT of the profile.
#
# Shell-sourceable KEY=VALUE, mirroring the targets.config idiom. Each profile carries EXACTLY two fields,
# resolved by prefix (eval "\$${profile}_PROFILE_...") — no other field is read:
#   <name>_PROFILE_DESCRIPTION       one-line human summary (shown at `start`)
#   <name>_PROFILE_EVIDENCE_DEFAULT  the evidence shape the architect defaults to: `dod_tests` | `assert`

# The set of legal profile names (space-separated); --profile is validated against this list.
INTAKE_PROFILES_LIST="${INTAKE_PROFILES_LIST:-code docs config}"

# --- code (default) — a runnable test is the natural Definition of Done ---
code_PROFILE_DESCRIPTION="Code change; the mechanical DoD is a runnable dod_tests selector."
code_PROFILE_EVIDENCE_DEFAULT="dod_tests"

# --- docs — prose/artifact work; a non-test sc_evidence assert is the natural DoD (P6a) ---
docs_PROFILE_DESCRIPTION="Docs/prose change; default to a non-test sc_evidence assert (contains/absent/sha256)."
docs_PROFILE_EVIDENCE_DEFAULT="assert"

# --- config — config/data change; a non-test sc_evidence assert over the changed file ---
config_PROFILE_DESCRIPTION="Config/data change; default to a non-test sc_evidence assert over the changed file."
config_PROFILE_EVIDENCE_DEFAULT="assert"
